00:10:49,658 --> 00:10:54,720
kind of a new religion or anything like that. It's really a set of mental tools and tricks.

203
00:10:55,401 --> 00:10:59,822
We're going to use cognitive science and reboot and build resilience in your brain.

204
00:11:00,563 --> 00:11:00,703
So,

205
00:11:01,430 --> 00:11:02,831
What do I mean when I say ritual?

206
00:11:03,412 --> 00:11:06,514
This is my definition of ritual for the purpose of this talk.

207
00:11:07,494 --> 00:11:09,556
A ritual involves words, signs, and actions

208
00:11:09,596 --> 00:11:11,157
that take you away from the mundane,

209
00:11:11,757 --> 00:11:14,058
crafting an intentional space for creative work

210
00:11:14,439 --> 00:11:15,199
and free thought.

211
00:11:16,960 --> 00:11:19,962
Some of the mental techniques involved around ritual

212
00:11:20,343 --> 00:11:22,044
can vary depending on what the ritual is.

213
00:11:22,084 --> 00:11:26,166
But there's a reason that it's so successful in human culture

214
00:11:26,266 --> 00:11:27,027
across the world.

215
00:11:27,467 --> 00:11:30,389
Almost every human society has elements of ritual.

216
00:11:31,072 --> 00:11:32,933
embedded in various aspects of their life.

217
00:11:33,493 --> 00:11:35,333
And they all have certain things in common.

218
00:11:36,453 --> 00:11:37,874
One of them is visualization,

219
00:11:38,534 --> 00:11:40,734
where you're picturing an outcome

220
00:11:41,334 --> 00:11:42,255
of the work that you're doing.

221
00:11:43,035 --> 00:11:45,035
Studies have shown that thoughts produce

222
00:11:45,055 --> 00:11:48,416
the same mental instructions and effects as actions do.

223
00:11:49,396 --> 00:11:53,257
And in fact, visualization, visualizing success,

224
00:11:53,337 --> 00:11:55,317
visualizing things being better,

225
00:11:55,377 --> 00:11:57,018
visualizing completing something.

226
00:11:57,960 --> 00:12:00,842
is actually, can actually enhance motivation,

227
00:12:00,942 --> 00:12:03,804
increase confidence and increase your efficiency.

228
00:12:03,904 --> 00:12:05,265
It improves your motor performance.

229
00:12:05,885 --> 00:12:07,286
It can increase the flow state.

230
00:12:07,806 --> 00:12:10,207
Visualization is actually a profound way

231
00:12:10,287 --> 00:12:12,148
to improve your success.

232
00:12:12,829 --> 00:12:14,110
And some studies, for example,

233
00:12:14,150 --> 00:12:17,211
showed that basketball players, this is the classic study,

234
00:12:17,612 --> 00:12:20,333
basketball players were split into two groups.

235
00:12:20,473 --> 00:12:22,614
One group practiced free throws

236
00:12:23,115 --> 00:12:26,377
and the other group visualized making free throws

237
00:12:26,417 --> 00:12:27,377
and didn't practice at all.

238
00:12:28,055 --> 00:12:30,337
And when they actually played the next day,

239
00:12:30,997 --> 00:12:33,840
those who visualized saw a slightly greater

240
00:12:33,960 --> 00:12:36,122
performance increase over those that practiced.

241
00:12:36,722 --> 00:12:37,703
It's that effective.

242
00:12:39,765 --> 00:12:42,127
Superstition is another element of ritual.

243
00:12:44,649 --> 00:12:47,472
And most people have a negative connotation to superstition,

244
00:12:47,512 --> 00:12:50,375
but I'd like to invite you to change your mind about that.

245
00:12:51,944 --> 00:12:55,647
An example of superstition is there was an experiment,

246
00:12:56,127 --> 00:12:57,969
actually two experiments around golf.

247
00:12:58,890 --> 00:13:02,633
In one experiment, people before they made a shot in golf

248
00:13:03,173 --> 00:13:05,435
were told that they had a lucky ball

249
00:13:05,595 --> 00:13:06,917
or that they had an ordinary ball.

250
00:13:07,857 --> 00:13:10,800
In the other experiment, before someone took their shot,

251
00:13:10,920 --> 00:13:12,261
either the moderator said nothing

252
