00:20:35,280 --> 00:20:38,763
And he opens it or has in it what he does every day

390
00:20:38,863 --> 00:20:39,683
as a part of his work.

391
00:20:40,804 --> 00:20:42,585
He says, I put on my lucky work boots

392
00:20:43,506 --> 00:20:45,907
and stitch them up with the lucky laces

393
00:20:45,927 --> 00:20:47,188
that my niece Meredith gave me.

394
00:20:47,208 --> 00:20:50,030
I head back to my office, crank up the computer.

395
00:20:50,690 --> 00:20:55,852
My lucky hooded sweatshirt is draped over the chair with the lucky charm I got in St. Marie de la Mer

396
00:20:56,352 --> 00:21:03,254
for only eight bucks. With my lucky Largo name tag that came from a dream I once had, I put it on.

397
00:21:04,034 --> 00:21:10,596
On my thesaurus is my lucky cannon that my friend Bob Forsandy gave me. I point it toward my chair

398
00:21:10,656 --> 00:21:15,757
so it can fire inspiration into me. I say my prayer which is the invocation of the muse from

399
00:21:15,797 --> 00:21:19,318
Homer's Odyssey. And it sits next to my shelf.

400
00:21:20,134 --> 00:21:25,536
with the cufflinks that belong to my father and my lucky acorn from the battlefield at Thermopylae.

