00:21:34,500 --> 00:21:40,902
I have a glass of water or a cup of tea. There's a certain time I sit down from 8 to 8 30 somewhere

403
00:21:40,942 --> 00:21:47,425
within a half hour every morning. I have my vitamin pill and my music. I sit in the same seat

404
00:21:48,160 --> 00:21:50,461
and the papers are all arranged in the same places.

405
00:21:52,482 --> 00:21:54,463
The cumulative purpose of doing these things

406
00:21:54,523 --> 00:21:57,844
the same way every day seems to be a way of saying to the mind,

407
00:21:57,864 --> 00:21:59,685
you're going to be dreaming soon.

408
00:22:00,805 --> 00:22:02,446
And that's really what the opening does.

409
00:22:03,166 --> 00:22:05,647
It sets a space in your mind.

410
00:22:05,707 --> 00:22:06,768
It creates that space.

411
00:22:06,848 --> 00:22:08,768
It frames your work, and it gives it purpose.

412
00:22:09,858 --> 00:22:11,959
But you need to figure out what matters to you.

